98":"1298","1275":"1275","about 1353":"about 1353","1328":"1328","Of Flamburgh, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Flamborough, Yorkshire, England":"Flamborough, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Constable","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (southeastern): occupational name for the law-enforcement officer of a parish, from Middle English, Old French <i>conestable</i>, <i>cunestable</i>, from Late Latin <i>comes stabuli</i> ‘officer of the stable’. The title was also borne by various other officials during the Middle Ages, including the chief officer of a household or court, or a military officer, and this may in some cases be the source of the surname.","Americanized form of Dutch <b>Constapel</b>, an occupational name for the chief gunner aboard a ship or in the garrison of a fort."],"variants":[{"name":"Costabile","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Aldo, Antonio, Ciro, Nino, Agnese, Angelo, Duilio, Enrico, Ercole, Franco, Palma.","Italian (southern):","occupational name from medieval Greek <i>kontostablēs</i> ‘chamberlain’, from medieval Latin <i>comes stabuli</i>, literally ‘count of the stable’ (see   Constable  )."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Constable was born about 1320, in Flamborough, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Marmaduke Constable I, was 47 and his mother, Elizabeth, was 44. He had at least 2 sons with Joan Fitz Hugh."},"et":{"Abt 1320–":"umbes 1320–Surnud","1298–Male":"1298–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1325–Female":"1325–Surnud","1315–1378":"1315–1378","1353–1401":"1353–1401","1275–1378":"1275–1378","1278–1328":"1278–1328","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1378":"1378","1278":"1278","Abt 1320":"umbes 1320","1353":"1353","1320":"1320","1298":"1298","1275":"1275","about 1353":"umbes 1353","1328":"1328","Of Flamburgh, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Flamborough, Yorkshire, England":"Flamborough, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1320–":"noin 1320–Kuollut","1298–Male":"1298–Kuollut","1320–Male":"1320–Kuollut","1325–Female":"1325–Kuollut","1315–1378":"1315–1378","1353–1401":"1353–1401","1275–1378":"1275–1378","1278–1328":"1278–1328","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1378":"1378","1278":"1278","Abt 1320":"noin 1320","1353":"1353","1320":"1320","1298":"1298","1275":"1275","about 1353":"noin 1353","1328":"1328","Of Flamburgh, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Flamborough, Yorkshire, England":"Flamborough, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1320–":"environ 1320–Décédé","1298–Male":"1298–Décédé","1320–Male":"1320–Décédé","1325–Female":"1325–Décédée","1315–1378":"1315–1378","1353–1401":"1353–1401","1275–1378":"1275–1378","1278–1328":"1278–1328","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","1401":"1401","1378":"1378","1278":"1278","Abt 1320":"environ 1320","1353":"1353","1320":"1320","1298":"1298","1275":"1275","about 1353":"environ 1353","1328":"1328","Of Flamburgh, Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Flamborough, Yorkshire, England":"Flamborough, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Constable est né environ 1320, à